shares in  Mediobanca SpA  to win regulatory approval for the
planned purchase of a stake in the company that controls insurer
 Fondiaria Sai SpA , Corriere della Sera reported, without saying
where it got the information.  Regulators may make the request because Mediobanca controls
Assicurazioni Generali SpA, Italyâ€™s largest insurer, according
to the weekly business supplement of the newspaper. Groupama
Chief Executive Officer  Jean Azema  also may have to leave his
